*/*` returned zero results. The `tsconfig.json` explicitly excludes it (`\"exclude\": [\"node_modules\", \"dist\", \"test\"]`), suggesting it was expected to exist at some point but was never created.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Is there a `test/setup/` directory with `test-app.factory.ts`, `test-database.ts`?\n\n**No.** No such directory or files exist.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Is there a `test/fixtures/` directory with `user.fixture.ts`, `auth.fixture.ts`?\n\n**No.** No such directory or files exist.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Is there a `test/mocks/` directory?\n\n**No.** No such directory exists.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Is there a `jest-e2e.json` file?\n\n**No.** No `jest-e2e.json` (or any `jest.config` file) exists anywhere. And there are **no test scripts** in `package.json`.\n\n---\n\n### 7. What modules exist under `src/modules/`?\n\nFive modules exist, but **only the entity layer has been implemented** — none have controllers, services, repositories, DTOs, or module definition files:\n\n| Module | Path | Contains |\n|--------|------|----------|\n| `auth` | `src/modules/auth/` | Only `entities/` with 2 entity files |\n| `favorites` | `src/modules/favorites/` | Only `entities/` with 1 entity file |\n| `inquiries` | `src/modules/inquiries/` | Only `entities/` with 1 entity file |\n| `properties` | `src/modules/properties/` | Only `entities/` with 4 entity files |\n| `users` | `src/modules/users/` | Only `entities/` with 1 entity file |\n\n**No controllers, services, repositories, DTOs, or module (`*.module.ts`) files exist in any module.**\n\n---\n\n### 8. What's in `src/core/`?\n\nThe core layer is **fully implemented** with all standard NestJS infrastructure:\n\n#### Base Classes (`src/core/base/`)\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| `base.entity.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.entity.ts` |\n| `base.repository.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.repository.ts` |\n| `base.service.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.service.ts` |\n| `base.controller.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/base.controller.ts` |\n| `index.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/base/index.ts` |\n\n**Key details:**\n- `BaseEntity` has `id` (UUID), `createdAt`, `updatedAt`, `deletedAt` (soft delete)\n- `BaseRepository<T>` wraps TypeORM `Repository` with CRUD methods (`findAll`, `findById`, `findOne`, `create`, `update`, `softDelete`, `delete`, `count`)\n- `BaseService<T>` adds `findByIdOrFail` (throws `NotFoundException`), calls repository methods\n- `BaseController<T>` has generic CRUD endpoints with Swagger decorators and `ParseUUIDPipe`\n\n#### Guards (`src/core/guards/`)\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| `jwt-auth.guard.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/guards/jwt-auth.guard.ts` |\n| `roles.guard.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/guards/roles.guard.ts` |\n| `jwt.strategy.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/guards/jwt.strategy.ts` |\n| `index.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/guards/index.ts` |\n\n**Key details:**\n- `JwtAuthGuard` extends `AuthGuard('jwt')`, respects `@Public()` decorator, returns 401 on failure\n- `RolesGuard` reads `@Roles(...)` metadata, checks `user.role` or `user.roles` array\n- `JwtStrategy` extracts JWT from httpOnly cookies first, then Bearer header as fallback; returns `{ id, email, role }`\n\n#### Decorators (`src/core/decorators/`)\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| `public.decorator.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/public.decorator.ts` |\n| `roles.decorator.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/roles.decorator.ts` |\n| `current-user.decorator.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/current-user.decorator.ts` |\n| `api-swagger.decorator.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/api-swagger.decorator.ts` |\n| `api-response-data.decorator.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/api-response-data.decorator.ts` |\n| `index.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/decorators/index.ts` |\n\n**Key details:**\n- `@Public()` marks routes as exempt from JWT authentication\n- `@Roles(...)` marks routes with required roles (string array)\n- `@CurrentUser()` / `@CurrentUser('id')` extracts authenticated user from request\n- `@ApiSwagger()` is a comprehensive decorator that auto-generates Swagger docs including auth, pagination, error responses\n- `@ApiResponseData()` wraps response DTOs in `ResponsePayloadDto` envelope for Swagger\n\n#### Filters (`src/core/filters/`)\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| `http-exception.filter.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/filters/http-exception.filter.ts` |\n| `all-exceptions.filter.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/filters/all-exceptions.filter.ts` |\n| `index.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/filters/index.ts` |\n\n**Key details:**\n- `HttpExceptionFilter` catches `HttpException` and returns structured `{ success, statusCode, message, data, timestamp, path }`\n- `AllExceptionsFilter` catches all other exceptions (non-HTTP), logs stack traces for unexpected errors\n\n#### Interceptors (`src/core/interceptors/`)\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| `transform.interceptor.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/interceptors/transform.interceptor.ts` |\n| `logging.interceptor.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/interceptors/logging.interceptor.ts` |\n| `set-token.interceptor.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/interceptors/set-token.interceptor.ts` |\n| `remove-token.interceptor.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/interceptors/remove-token.interceptor.ts` |\n| `index.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/interceptors/index.ts` |\n\n**Key details:**\n- `TransformInterceptor` wraps all responses in `{ success, statusCode, message, data, timestamp, path }` envelope (skips double-wrapping)\n- `LoggingInterceptor` logs `[HTTP] GET /api/users 200 +45ms` for each request\n- `SetTokenInterceptor` sets httpOnly cookies for access and refresh tokens on login/register\n- `RemoveTokenInterceptor` clears both cookie types on logout\n\n#### Pipes (`src/core/pipes/`)\n| File | Path |\n|------|------|\n| `validation.pipe.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/pipes/validation.pipe.ts` |\n| `index.ts` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/core/pipes/index.ts` |\n\nPre-configured `ValidationPipe` with `whitelist`, `forbidNonWhitelisted`, `transform`, and implicit conversion enabled.\n\n---\n\n### 9. What entities exist?\n\n**9 entity files across 5 modules + 1 base:**\n\n| Entity | Path | Table | Extends |\n|--------|------|-------|---------|\n| `BaseEntity` (abstract) | `src/core/base/base.entity.ts` | N/A | N/A |\n| `User` | `src/modules/users/entities/user.entity.ts` | `users` | `BaseEntity` |\n| `RefreshToken` | `src/modules/auth/entities/refresh-token.entity.ts` | `refresh_tokens` | (standalone) |\n| `PasswordResetToken` | `src/modules/auth/entities/password-reset-token.entity.ts` | `password_reset_tokens` | (standalone) |\n| `Property` | `src/modules/properties/entities/property.entity.ts` | `properties` | `BaseEntity` |\n| `PropertyPhoto` | `src/modules/properties/entities/property-photo.entity.ts` | `property_photos` | `BaseEntity` |\n| `Amenity` | `src/modules/properties/entities/amenity.entity.ts` | `amenities` | `BaseEntity` |\n| `PropertyAmenity` | `src/modules/properties/entities/property-amenity.entity.ts` | `property_amenities` | (standalone, composite PK) |\n| `Favorite` | `src/modules/favorites/entities/favorite.entity.ts` | `favorites` | `BaseEntity` |\n| `Inquiry` | `src/modules/inquiries/entities/inquiry.entity.ts` | `inquiries` | `BaseEntity` |\n\n**Entity relationships:**\n- `User` 1:N `RefreshToken`, 1:N `PasswordResetToken`, 1:N `Favorite`, 1:N `Inquiry`\n- `Property` 1:N `PropertyPhoto`, 1:N `PropertyAmenity`, 1:N `Favorite`, 1:N `Inquiry`\n- `Amenity` 1:N `PropertyAmenity`\n- `PropertyAmenity` has composite primary key (`propertyId`, `amenityId`)\n\n**Key entities that extend `BaseEntity`:** User, Property, PropertyPhoto, Amenity, Favorite, Inquiry\n**Standalone entities (own PK/columns):** RefreshToken, PasswordResetToken, PropertyAmenity\n\n---\n\n### 10. What does the `package.json` look like?\n\n**Path:** `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/package.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"backend\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc --noEmit\",\n    \"build\": \"tsc\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@nestjs/common\": \"^10.3.0\",\n    \"@nestjs/core\": \"^10.3.0\",\n    \"@nestjs/swagger\": \"^11.4.3\",\n    \"@nestjs/typeorm\": \"^10.0.2\",\n    \"class-transformer\": \"^0.5.1\",\n    \"class-validator\": \"^0.14.1\",\n    \"reflect-metadata\": \"^0.2.2\",\n    \"rxjs\": \"^7.8.1\",\n    \"typeorm\": \"^0.3.20\"\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@types/node\": \"^20.12.7\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.4.5\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Critical observation:** There are **NO test scripts** at all. Missing from scripts:\n- No `test` script\n- No `test:e2e` script\n- No `test:cov` script\n- No `start`, `start:dev`, or `start:prod` scripts either\n\n**Missing dependencies for testing:**\n- No `jest` / `@jest/globals`\n- No `@nestjs/testing`\n- No `ts-jest`\n- No `supertest` / `@nestjs/supertest`\n- No `@types/jest`\n- No `@types/supertest`\n\n**Other missing dependencies:**\n- No `@nestjs/jwt` (needed by `TokenService` and `JwtStrategy`)\n- No `@nestjs/passport` / `passport` / `passport-jwt` (needed by `JwtStrategy`)\n- No `@nestjs/config` (needed by `SetTokenInterceptor` and `TokenModule`)\n- No `dotenv` (needed by `env-config.service.ts`)\n- No `pg` (needed for TypeORM PostgreSQL)\n\n---\n\n### 11. Search for any existing `*.e2e-spec.ts` or `*.spec.ts` files\n\n**Zero test files exist.** Glob searches for both patterns returned no results:\n- `backend/**/*.e2e-spec.ts` — **0 files**\n- `backend/**/*.spec.ts` — **0 files**\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Project State Assessment\n\nThe backend is in a **very early stage of development**. Here's a breakdown:\n\n**Implemented:**\n- Entity layer (9 entities + 1 base class) — fully defined with all relationships and indexes\n- Core infrastructure (base classes, guards, decorators, filters, interceptors, pipes) — complete\n- Configuration layer (`env-config.service.ts`, `jwt.config.ts`)\n- Shared DTOs and interfaces (`ResponsePayloadDto`, `PaginationDto`, `IJwtPayload`)\n- Database migration (`001-initial-schema.ts`) — complete with all 7 tables\n- Token infrastructure (`TokenService`, `TokenModule`)\n- Enums (`RoleEnum`, `UserStatusEnum`, `PropertyTypeEnum`, `InquiryStatusEnum`)\n- Entry points (`main.ts`, `app.module.ts`) — minimal stubs\n\n**Not Implemented:**\n- Module-level files: **0 controllers, 0 services, 0 repositories, 0 DTOs, 0 modules**\n- Testing infrastructure: **0 test files, 0 test fixtures, 0 mocks, no jest config, no test scripts**\n- Package dependencies for JWT, Passport, config, database driver are missing from `package.json`\n- No `start`/`dev`/`prod` run scripts\n</task_result>","metadata":{"parentSessionId":"ses_1c05bffceffeMr1RceXLVElxnf","sessionId":"ses_1c05bb795ffeOuyx2m3qcC3aaJ","model":{"modelID":"deepseek-v4-pro","providerID":"opencode-go"},"trunc